<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Arm-Circle">Arm Circle</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/arm-circle" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">arm circle</a> exercise works the pectoralis major and minor, deltoids, and serratus anterior muscles. These are important for pushing and lifting heavy objects.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The main benefits of the arm circle exercise are improving muscle tone, joint mobility, and posture. <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8071570/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Muscle tone</a> is the balance of elasticity and stiffness in a muscle. Having an imbalance of muscle elasticity and stiffness can lead to various injuries.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Arm Circles" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980200840?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arm Circle Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin in a standing position, feet shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Raise your arms directly forward in front of you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Continue to raise above your head.</li>



<li>Continue to rotate your arms behind your head until you reach back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Continue steps 2–4 until goal repetitions are met.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Exhale as you initially lift your arms upward. Inhale on the backward motion behind your head.</li>



<li>Limit range of motion if you experience pain or discomfort. You can do this by not lifting your arms as high or by removing the backward motion.</li>



<li>Incorporate this exercise into your upper body warm-up or into your general routine workout.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



